article.description: JD Notae made 2 of 3 free throws with 0.5 seconds left and finished with 20 points to help Jacksonville beat Stetson 68-67 on Monday night.
article.headline: Notae's FTs with 0.5 left lift Jacksonville over Stetson
article.linkText: Notae's FTs with 0.5 left lift Jacksonville over Stetson
article.story: DELAND, Fla. -- JD Notae made 2 of 3 free throws with 0.5 seconds left and finished with 20 points to help Jacksonville beat Stetson 68-67 on Monday night. Devin Harris had 14 points, 10 rebounds, seven assists and three steals, Jace Hogan also scored 14 and Jalyn Hinton added 12 points on 5-of-6 shooting for Jacksonville (12-13, 6-2 Atlantic Sun). Stetson's Luke Doyle banked in a straightaway, NBA-range 3 to take a 67-66 lead with 4.5 seconds to play, but Notae was fouled on a 3-point attempt and his free throws sealed it. Hinton scored six points and Notae hit back-to-back 3s during a 13-0 run that gave Jacksonville a 57-47 lead with eight minutes to go. Divine Myles scored five points during a 12-5 spurt that pulled Stetson within two points with 1:22 remaining and the Dolphins held on, despite making just 5 of 11 free throws from there. Doyle led the Hatters (10-15, 2-6) with 16 points, including five 3-pointers, and Myles finished with 16.
